Instead of using an `alias`, you should keep the theorem on the original form as written. That minimizes the number of downstream problems.
Can you change `type_subrel_lt` to use `Iio` too?
Can the `@` be dropped here and/or below?
No, although I'm not sure why (it seems to correctly fill the implicit argument with `Ordinal` but then fail to synth the well order of the subtype).

`type` and `typein` both need the explicit type argument when being used with any sort of polymorphic notation. I've thought about making a PR to turn them into explicit args but I haven't come around to that.
This could be a `simp` lemma :)
